<item>
            <title>[JDK-8315652] RISC-V: Features string uses wrong separator for jtreg</title>
                <link>https://bugs.openjdk.org/browse/JDK-8315652</link>
                <project id="10100" key="JDK">JDK</project>
                    <description>The other platforms use space or comma space.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The WB class CPUInfo.java gives you the features in a List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; which is not working (as in one features per list item) on RV.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
The jtreg requires annotation allows you regexp the string of that list to determine if required feature is on current CPU.&lt;br/&gt;
Without separator it is not easy to match e.g. vector.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
If we use plain space.&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;rv64 i g c v zicbop z...&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
For the requires annotation that means the string we are regexping looks like:&lt;br/&gt;
[rv64, i, m, a, f, d, c, v, zicbom, zicboz, zicbop, zba, zbb, zbs, zicsr, zifencei, zic64b, zihintpause]&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We can then use required tag, such as:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;* @requires vm.cpu.features ~= &amp;quot;.* v,.*&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
which should only match vector.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
But that would mean CPU info/desc looks &amp;#39;funny&amp;#39; for RV folks:&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;quot;CPU: total 16 (initial active 16) rv64 i m a f d c v zicbom zicboz zicbop zba zbb zbs zicsr zifencei zic64b zihintpause&amp;quot;&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
